post_text:
Students and Parents,

The Miller School District and Cox Health will be hosting a Sports Physical day on July 28th at Miller High School from 8:00AM-3:00PM. Physicals will be administered on a first come first serve basis. Please see the attached documents regarding forms and payment information. If you have Medicaid coverage, no insurance, or qualify for free or reduced lunches, THE PHYSICAL IS FREE OF CHARGE. Otherwise, the physical will be $10.

Please pull up to the front of the HS and you will be greeted with further instructions. Students and parents will remain in the parking lot and will be let in one at a time. Cox Health will be requiring all students and parents wear masks during the physical. Masks will be provided. All paperwork must be filled out prior to the physical or a parent must be present to complete the form on site. No cash will be accepted on site. Payment information is included in the attached form.

Thank you and we are looking forward to another successful year of Miller Athletics.

post_text:
This afternoon, Governor Parsons announced that all Missouri public and charter schools are to remain closed through the remainder of the 2019-2020 academic year.

The Miller R-2 School District plans to continue to provide meals and continue to make additional learning enhancement opportunities available for students. In addition, the Miller R-2 School District is looking at rescheduling graduation to another date later this summer. Information will be shared when it becomes available.

We appreciate everyone’s patience and understanding.

Sincerely,
Dustin Storm

post_text: Yesterday, the Miller R-2 School District began providing meals for our students. We served over 120 students between meal pick up and delivery. Thank you to all of our volunteers that helped make this possible. If you would like to participate in the meal program call into today at the Elementary office at 417-452-3512 and we will add you to the list. This program is for students 18 and under in the Miller R-2 School District, no student will be turned away regardless of calling ahead. We will be serving again today from 11:00-12:30 and the program will continue Monday through Friday next week.

shared_text:
Miller Cardinal Archery
February 23 at 12:19 AM ·

Billings MO

Another fantastic year for MILLER Cardinal Archery at the Southwest Invitational Tournament in Billings. An announcement was made following the competition that this was one of the toughest events they have ever held.

Athena Cooper shot a career high of 293 to clinch 1st place in the HS Girls division and 1st place high scoring female of the tournament. Ethan McCracken shot a 282 to secure 1st place in the JH boys division and gain him his second win of the year. Several others improved considerably and had a great competition as well. As usual, every member of this team conducted themselves as good citizens at the event and should make MILLER proud!

shared_text:
Miller Cardinal Archery
February 8 at 11:22 PM ·

Crane MO
13 schools competing

Congratulations to JR Strait and Ethan McCracken for an awesome job today at the Crane Tournament! JR shot a career high of 289 to secure the number 1 spot for HS Boys shooting 19 tens. Ethan clinched the number 1 position for JH Boys with a tie at 283 but had 18 tens, 4 over his opponent.

Athena Cooper held a top 5 spot with a 277 in the HS Girls division and Deborah Browning moved into the top 10 JH Girls with a 259.

We had several career bests today and there are some shooters working hard and gaining experience that will pay off soon!
